                            <comment id="111216" author="sbrannen" created="Thu, 8 Jan 2015 04:11:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This proposal is very similar to Spring&apos;s existing support for the &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationContextInitializer&lt;/tt&gt; API.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fact, your proposed &lt;tt&gt;ContextDecorator&lt;/tt&gt; is basically identical to the API for &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationContextInitializer&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please take a look at &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationContextInitializer&lt;/tt&gt; &amp;#8211; which is configured via &lt;tt&gt;@ContextConfiguration(initializers=...)&lt;/tt&gt; &amp;#8211; and let us know if that meets your needs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note however that initializers are invoked in &lt;tt&gt;AbstractGenericContextLoader.loadContext(MergedContextConfiguration)&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;em&gt;before&lt;/em&gt; bean definitions are loaded, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you truly require access to the context immediately prior to refresh, you will have to extend one of the concrete subclasses of &lt;tt&gt;AbstractGenericContextLoader&lt;/tt&gt; and override the &lt;tt&gt;customizeContext()&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an alternative, you should consider implementing a custom &lt;tt&gt;TestExecutionListener&lt;/tt&gt; and registering it via &lt;tt&gt;@TestExecutionListeners&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please let us know your thoughts in light of this additional information.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="111217" author="sbrannen" created="Thu, 8 Jan 2015 04:20:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As an aside, you mentioned that you would like to create &lt;em&gt;custom test annotations&lt;/em&gt;, but your proposed &lt;tt&gt;ContextDecorator&lt;/tt&gt; API does not provide a way to access the test class or test method that is currently being executed. It only provides implementers access to the &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationContext&lt;/tt&gt;. So I don&apos;t see how you intend to perform any actions based on &lt;em&gt;custom test annotations&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In general, if you wish to provide additional functionality to tests based on &lt;em&gt;custom test annotations&lt;/em&gt;, you should implement a &lt;tt&gt;TestExecutionListener&lt;/tt&gt;: a &lt;tt&gt;TestExecutionListener&lt;/tt&gt; is given a reference to the current &lt;tt&gt;TestContext&lt;/tt&gt; which provides access to the test class and test method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
